- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): Smoothed Particle Hydrodynamics is a numerical method commonly used in computational fluid dynamics and other engineering/science applications.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses parallelization of the SPH simulations on hybrid shared/distributed-memory architectures, which falls under this category.
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper proposes a new algorithm for neighbour-finding in SPH simulations, which involves mathematical computations and software implementation.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the numerical method of Smoothed Particle Hydrodynamics and proposes a new algorithm for its implementation.
- cs.SC (Scientific Computing): The paper discusses the use of SPH simulations in scientific computing and proposes a new algorithm for its implementation on parallel architectures.
